  "text": "To date, only few studies have addressed this question of intradimensional bottom-up capture concerning color. [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] presented an irrelevant color-singleton distractor away from the color target during color search. Importantly, the distractor color was certain, but both studies nonetheless demonstrated interference by the color-singleton distractor during color search. However, both studies only measured manual response times (RTs). Therefore, it cannot be ruled out that the distractor interference reflected nonspatial filtering costs rather than attention capture by the distractor [CITATION_3] . Nonspatial filtering costs are RT costs due to feature (e.g., color) heterogeneity in the display that slows down the decision about where to move spatial attention.",
